        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-03-17 23:33:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nThis looks good to me too.\nAndreas' comment is pretty valid too.\nWould you like to have a separate patch patching the patches, or would you prefer to update this one?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5e8111959807f20a26f293404445bf24d8efede9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 7,
        "name": "Johann Lombardi",
        "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
        "username": "johann",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-24 13:55:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI still would like to land this patch if you don't mind.\nI am working on another patch to kill iopen and i am going to remove the vfs_races patch at the same time, which means that we will always use the DCACHE_LUSTRE_INVALID defined in lustre.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
